Sentencas: The potential application of combined EDTA-citrate complexing process (ECCP) in intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) processing was investigated.
Titulo: Anode-supported ScSZ-electrolyte SOFC with whole cell materials from combined EDTA-citrate complexing synthesis process

Sentencas: ECCP-derived scandia-stabilized-zirconia (ScSZ) powder displayed low packing density, high surface area and nanocrystalline, which was ideal material for thin-film electrolyte fabrication based on dual dry pressing.
Titulo: Anode-supported ScSZ-electrolyte SOFC with whole cell materials from combined EDTA-citrate complexing synthesis process

Sentencas: A co-synthesis of NiO + ScSZ anode based on ECCP was developed, which showed reduced NiO(Ni) and ScSZ grain sizes and improved homogeneity of the particle size distribution, as compared with the mechanically mixed NiO + ScSZ anode.
Titulo: Anode-supported ScSZ-electrolyte SOFC with whole cell materials from combined EDTA-citrate complexing synthesis process

Sentencas: Anode-supported ScSZ electrolyte fuel cell with the whole cell materials synthesized from ECCP was successfully prepared.
Titulo: Anode-supported ScSZ-electrolyte SOFC with whole cell materials from combined EDTA-citrate complexing synthesis process

Sentencas: The porous anode and cathode exhibited excellent adhesion to the electrolyte layer.
Titulo: Anode-supported ScSZ-electrolyte SOFC with whole cell materials from combined EDTA-citrate complexing synthesis process

Sentencas: Fuel cell with 30 mu m thick ScSZ electrolyte and La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 cathode showed a promising maximum peak power density of 350 mWcm(-2) at 800 degrees C. (c) 2007
Titulo: Anode-supported ScSZ-electrolyte SOFC with whole cell materials from combined EDTA-citrate complexing synthesis process
